<li>
	<H4>Steps</H4>
	<H5>Stage-1</H5>	
		<b>Step-1:</b> Create DARE working directories and cactus build directories<br/>
		<b>Step-2:</b> Transfer thorn-file and parameter-file to remote machine<br/>
		<b>Step-3:</b> Downnload Getcomponents via WGET<br/>
		<b>Step-4:</b> Run Getcomponents with the given thornfile <br/>
		<b>Step-5:</b> Now transfer the cactus_installer.py file ("cactus_installer.py" checks for the executable 'cactus_sim' exists or not and builds cactus if necessary.)<br/>
		<b>Step-6:</b> run cactus_installer.py to actually build cactus with downloded thorns if necessary.<br/>

	<H5>Stage-2</H5>	                  
		<b>Step-1(7):</b> Create cactus simulation directory<br/>
		<b>Step-2(8):</b> Run cactus simulation through cactus mpi and given parameter file<br/>
		<b>Step-3(9):</b> Tar the output parameter file<br/>
		<b>Step-4(10):</b>Transfer the output file back to this server. <br/>

	
</li>




<li>
	<H4>Advantages</H4>
	<p>
		Usability and Scalability along with faster results due to Distributed Computing
	</p>
